A 20-year-old man has died in hospital after being taken ill at Global Gathering dance festival.

An investigation has been launched after the man fell ill on the first night of the two-day event at Long Marston airfield near Stratford-upon-Avon, Warwickshire.

Police said the man was taken from the festival site to Warwick Hospital at about 11pm last night but was pronounced dead at 1am after attempts to save him failed.

