She said: ‘Everyone at GlobalGathering is deeply saddened by this tragic news.

‘Our sincerest thoughts and condolences are with the family and friends at this time.

‘We are assisting Warwickshire Police with their ongoing investigation.’

The man’s death came as temperatures soared to 28C in Stratford-upon-Avon today and 30C in other parts of the country.

Police have been issuing regular warnings to festival-goers to drink plenty of water so as not to get too dehydrated in the heat. 

